sts involved. The Brewers faced criticism and hostility from mayor Richard Whittington, which are documented vividly. The Brewers supplied ale to the household of Queen Katherine and for her coronation. The clerk wrote an account of the funeral processions for King Henry V in 1422 in London and Westminster, noting the role played by the London crafts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBrewing industryzEnglandzLondonxHistoryvSources. 4aBritish Local History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aAle brewing.  aAlmshouses.  aBrewers of London.  aBrewers’ Book.  aBrewers’ clerk.  aChurch of St Mary Aldermanbury.  aCraft and Fraternity of Brewers.  aCraft.  aFraternity.  aInns, taverns and brewhouses.  aKing Henry V.  aMayor Richard Whittington.  aMedieval.  aMemorandum Book.  aMistery.  aTrade.  aWilliam Porlond.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143096640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805431176?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805431176423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805431176/original  a978-3-11-143096-6  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles